      "Figure 2 shows the speedup of the model on the T3D for a fixed-size problem."
    ],
    "justification": "The paper explicitly describes a 'parallel ocean model' designed for 'massively parallel processing (MPP) platforms', which are HPC clusters. It details the parallelization strategy ('domain decomposition') and provides performance results, including 'speedup' on specific supercomputers of the era (CM-5 and T3D). This directly aligns with the Level 2 criteria of a parallel model that scales on HPC clusters.",
    "paper_doi": "10.1016/B978-044482322-9/50121-3",
    "paper_title": "Application of a parallel Navier-Stokes model to ocean circulation"
  },
