    "justification": "The paper validates the results of its observational model (acoustic tomography) by comparing them against independent, real-world data from a nearly simultaneous hydrographic cruise. The comparison is not merely qualitative; it provides a direct statistical comparison of a global metric (the total heat content across the section), including mean values and their uncertainties. The calculated values from the two methods show a very small bias and agree within the stated error bars. This quantitative, statistical comparison against independent data meets the criteria for Level 2.",
