    "justification": "The authors employ a \"standard linear stochastic inverse method\" to derive their temperature estimates. This method explicitly incorporates prior information (a climatology with mean and covariance) and data uncertainties (standard deviations of daily-mean travel times) to produce \"formal error estimates\" for the final quantities. This technique is a form of optimal interpolation or objective analysis, which is mathematically equivalent to Bayesian inference under Gaussian assumptions. It combines a prior distribution with a likelihood function to generate a posterior distribution for the estimated quantities, from which the error bounds are derived. This formal probabilistic approach aligns with the description of a Level 3 (Probabilistic) methodology.",
