    "justification": "The paper presents several idealized test cases where the model's numerical results are compared against known analytical solutions or theoretical predictions. These include comparing the front speed in a lock-exchange problem to the Benjamin formula, comparing the internal wave field to Long's linear theory, and comparing heat flux in a convection simulation to established scaling laws. These comparisons with analytical solutions and theoretical benchmarks are a form of 'exact benchmarks' that test the fundamental algorithmic correctness of the code, which aligns with the Level 3 criteria.",
