      "The inversion result obtained after one iteration is also shown in Fig. 2 (bottom panel). It is seen that the reconstruction of the eddy is very good.",
      "To check the dependence of the solution on the choice of the reference field c0, the inversion was repeated using a different reference field... From Fig. 3 it is seen that the reconstruction of the eddy is equally good in both cases."
    ],
    "justification": "The authors verify their inversion algorithm using a synthetic data test, also known as an 'identical twin' experiment. They define a known 'true' ocean state (a sound-speed field), use their forward model to simulate the expected travel-time data, and then feed this synthetic data into their inversion algorithm to check if it can recover the original 'true' state. This constitutes a structured, system-level regression test. Furthermore, they investigate the dependence of the inversion result on the initial guess (the reference field), which is a form of convergence or robustness study. These activities\u2014using structured tests with known solutions (regression tests) and performing convergence-related studies\u2014directly align with the criteria for Level 2.",
