    "dimension": "sustainability",
    "has_evidence": true,
    "evidence_level": 2,
    "evidence_passages": [
      "A key part of a modern modelling effort involves the development of a documented and flexible model code. This need led the US climate modelling community to formulate the Community Climate System Model (CCSM) project. A key component of this project is the development of a flexible, well-documented, and portable ocean code.",
      "The MOM code is another descendant from the GFDL suite of models. It is widely used by many groups around the world.",
      "The UK ocean modelling community has recently adopted a version of the OPA code for its climate studies."
