    "justification": "The paper highlights a clear shift towards community-driven and sustainable software practices for the time (2000). It explicitly states the importance of \"documented and flexible model code\" and describes the formation of the Community Climate System Model (CCSM) project to develop such a resource. The mention of models being \"widely used by many groups\" and adopted by entire national communities (e.g., OPA in the UK) points to a healthy community and a maintained codebase that is shared and supported, aligning well with Level 2 criteria. While specific modern tools like Git or public repositories are not mentioned, the described community efforts to create documented, portable, and widely used codes serve the same purpose and represent a \"Maintained\" level of sustainability. The evidence does not support Level 3 as there is no mention of institutional practices like CI/CD or long-term roadmaps.",
