    "evidence_passages": [
      "The purpose of this paper is to document a method that retains the computational benefits of an explicit time-stepping scheme for the free surface while also maintaining global tracer conservation.",
      "The nonconservation arises from a mismatch between the transport used to advect tracers and the transport used to compute the sea surface height.",
      "This artifice of T* allows us to write the tracer tendency equation in a manifestly conservative flux form, which is a key to its utility.",
      "The new conservative method reduces this drift to less than 10\u207b\u00b9\u2074 C per century, which is at the level of machine precision."
    ],
    "justification": "The paper is explicitly focused on fixing a numerical \"leak\" that causes non-conservation of tracers in ocean models. The authors propose a new method based on a \"manifestly conservative flux form,\" which is a technique specifically designed to ensure budgets are strictly closed. The success of their method is demonstrated by reducing unphysical tracer drift to \"the level of machine precision.\" This result is a clear example of achieving the Level 3 criterion of \"Strictly Closed Budgets.\"",
