    "justification": "The paper focuses exclusively on the numerical methods for tracer conservation within a z-coordinate ocean model, specifically concerning the implementation of an explicit free surface. It details modifications to the model's governing equations to ensure physical consistency. The paper does not discuss or describe any methods for integrating observational data with the model logic, such as data assimilation (e.g., Kalman Filter, 4D-Var) or forcing methodologies. The test cases mentioned use idealized forcing (e.g., wind stress, relaxation to a profile) to drive the model, but these are presented as part of the experimental setup to validate the numerical scheme, not as a topic of investigation for data integration. The core contribution of the paper is on the model's internal dynamics and numerics, not on how the model interacts with external observational data. Therefore, there is no evidence relevant to the Data Integration dimension.",
