    "evidence_passages": [
      "To test the free surface methods, we consider an idealized two-dimensional (x, z) channel model with a flat bottom. The domain is 1000 km in the zonal direction and 5000 m deep. The grid spacing is uniform with 100 horizontal points and 50 vertical points. The initial sea surface height is a Gaussian-shaped sea surface height anomaly centered in the channel... The tracer is initialized to be linearly dependent on the vertical coordinate z...",
      "As seen in Fig. 1, the total tracer content for the virtual salt flux method is not conserved. Instead, there is a spurious drift away from the initial value.",
      "The real salt/freshwater flux method, however, conserves the total tracer content to within machine precision, as seen in Fig. 1."
