      "The method used here is a four\u2010dimensional (4D) variational method (Le Dimet and Talagrand 1986).",
      "The variational method aims at finding the model trajectory that is closest to both the model dynamics and the available observations over a time interval (the assimilation window).",
      "The problem is formulated as the minimization of a cost function J, which has to be minimized with respect to the initial conditions. J is defined by the sum of two terms: J = Jo + Jb. The first term, Jo, measures the misfit between the model and the observations. The second term, Jb, measures the distance to a background or first\u2010guess solution."
