    "justification": "The paper exclusively uses a 'twin experiment' methodology. In this setup, a model simulation is defined as the 'true ocean', and synthetic observations are generated from this simulation. The assimilation is then tested on its ability to recover this known 'true' model state. This approach tests the internal consistency and performance of the data assimilation system, not the model's predictive skill against real-world data. Therefore, no evidence for the Validation dimension is present.",
