    "evidence_passages": [
      "A key aspect in the successful exploitation of satellite altimetry is its validation and combination with other geodetic data. For validation of altimetry derived gravity information ship gravity data are usually considered as the most appropriate reference. Ship gravity data are independent from altimetry and provide comparable accuracy in terms of gravity anomalies.",
      "Another important validation is the comparison of altimetry-derived geoid heights with geoid heights derived from GPS positioning on benchmarks with known heights from spirit levelling. This is presently the most accurate method to get absolute geoid information.",
