    "justification": "The paper describes a comprehensive validation process using multiple, independent datasets. It explicitly mentions using independent ship gravity data (a global, though heterogeneous, dataset) and GPS/levelling data as the 'most appropriate reference' and 'most accurate method' for validating altimetry-derived gravity anomalies and geoid heights, respectively. The paper also presents the results of these comparisons statistically (mean, standard deviation of differences), demonstrating a rigorous, quantitative assessment. This process of validating against independent, global-scale datasets aligns with the criteria for Level 3.",
