      "The method is known as least squares collocation. It provides an optimal estimate in the sense that the variance of the estimation error is minimized. ... The error of the estimated signal can also be derived. The variance is given by: D(s\u02c6) = C(ss) - C(st)C(tt)\u207b\u00b9C(ts).",
      "Figure 6 shows the corresponding error standard deviation of the mean sea surface. One can clearly see the data gaps (e.g. at the north pole) where the error is maximal (equal to the a-priori variance of the signal)."
