    "justification": "The paper employs a formal probabilistic approach to uncertainty quantification. It explicitly defines a stochastic model for observation errors using covariance functions. The methodology used, least-squares collocation, is a statistical estimation technique that not only provides an optimal estimate but also formally derives the error variance of that estimate. The paper provides the specific equation for computing this error variance and presents the results as error maps (e.g., maps of error standard deviation). This formal, model-based derivation and quantification of error variance is a clear example of a Level 3 (Probabilistic) approach.",
