    "dimension": "data_integration",
    "has_evidence": true,
    "evidence_level": 3,
    "evidence_passages": [
      "The GRACE gravity field solutions are provided in the form of spherical harmonic (SH) coefficients, typically estimated over a certain time span (e.g., 10 days or 1 month). The CSR Release-01 (RL01) monthly gravity solutions used in this study are computed using GRACE K-band ranging (KBR), attitude, and GPS data collected over approximately 30-day intervals. The gravity estimation procedure is based on a least squares adjustment of a set of normal equations accumulated over the same 30-day interval."
    ],
    "justification": "The paper describes the method for generating GRACE gravity fields as a \"least squares adjustment of a set of normal equations accumulated over the same 30-day interval.\" This is a batch processing method where all observations within a one-month window are used simultaneously to solve for the gravity field parameters that best fit the data, subject to the physical laws of orbital mechanics. This approach, where a time series of data and the physical model are combined in a single mathematical inversion, is a form of synthesis. It is characteristic of Level 3, where data and physics are mathematically inseparable, similar to 4D-Var.",
    "paper_doi": "10.1029/2004GL021670",
