    ],
    "justification": "The paper verifies the GRACE data processing results by comparing specific outputs (degree-2 spherical harmonic coefficients) against results from independent, established techniques like Satellite Laser Ranging (SLR) and Atmospheric Angular Momentum (AAM) models. This cross-verification against independent benchmarks serves as a high-level regression test, confirming that the GRACE processing yields results consistent with other trusted methods for quantities they both can measure. This structured comparison supports a Level 2 assessment.",
