    "justification": "The paper describes a modeling protocol where ocean-ice models are 'forced' by a common atmospheric dataset. This is the definition of a Level 1 'Forced' approach where the model is driven by data. Additionally, the protocol explicitly calls for 'weak restoring of sea surface salinity (SSS) to climatological values'. This technique, also known as nudging, directly alters the model state to match a data product (a climatology), which is characteristic of a Level 1 system and can violate the model's physical conservation principles. No evidence of more advanced sequential (Level 2) or synthesis (Level 3) data assimilation methods is present.",
