    "justification": "The paper, in describing the CORE protocol, provides examples of model validation that fit the Level 3 criteria. The validation is performed against multiple independent, global observational datasets, including the World Ocean Atlas 2005 (WOA05) for temperature and salinity, and satellite-based SSM/I observations for sea-ice. Critically, the analysis goes beyond global metrics to assess key physical processes. This includes a process-level comparison of the Atlantic Meridional Overturning Circulation (AMOC) against in-situ observational array data (RAPID/MOCHA) and an evaluation of the model's skill in reproducing major modes of climate variability (NAO and PDO). This combination of using independent global datasets and evaluating specific physical processes represents a high level of validation.",
