      "Table 2 gives the mean transport and the standard deviations of the three models and the observations for the 17 month overlapping period. The mean transport is southward for all time series, with a value of \u221216.7 Sv for the observations. The SODA model has a mean transport of \u221216.4 Sv, which is very close to the observed mean transport.",
      "Table 3 gives the correlation coefficients and the root-mean-square error (RMSE) between the transport time series of the observations and the models. The correlation between the observations and OCCAM is the highest (0.39), but still very low. ... This is confirmed by the high RMSE values for all three models.",
      "A spectral analysis of the time series reveals that all models have a transport variability which is dominated by the same frequency band (60\u2013120 days) as the observations. All models also show a second peak at a period of about 30\u201340 days, which is absent in the observations.",
      "To examine how well the models represent the observed eddy statistics, the time series of the transports were filtered with a 30 day low\u2010pass filter to remove the high\u2010frequency variability. Subsequently, eddies were defined as the periods in which the transport exceeded a certain threshold (1 standard deviation from the mean). Table 4 gives the eddy statistics of the observations and the models."
    ],
