      "Because the Arctic is a region of low salinity, the sea surface height anomaly (SSHA) is dominated by the halosteric component... We therefore use SSHA as a proxy for the FWC anomaly, \u0394FWC... We obtain a relationship between the change in FWC and the change in sea level, \u0394FWC = 1.63 x 10^12 \u0394SSHA, with a correlation coefficient of 0.94 and a standard error on the slope of 0.08 x 10^12.",
