    ],
    "justification": "The paper validates a simple physical model (time integral of Ekman pumping velocity) against real-world satellite data (sea surface height anomaly). The authors quantify the agreement with statistical metrics, specifically a correlation coefficient (0.92) and a root mean square (r.m.s.) difference (2.1 cm). The use of r.m.s. difference, which is equivalent to RMSE, is a clear indicator of a Level 2 statistical validation.",
    "paper_doi": "10.1038/NGEO1379",
