      "We use satellite radar altimeter data from the European Remote Sensing satellites ERS-1 and ERS-2, and Envisat. We use a conventional pulse-limited retracking algorithm to reprocess the ERS-1 and ERS-2 radar altimeter waveforms over the Arctic Ocean north of 65\u25e6 N between 1995 and 2003, and the Envisat waveforms between 2002 and 2010. Retracking the raw radar returns provides more accurate sea-ice elevation measurements than using the standard satellite data products."
