      "This paper describes an analysis of three different versions of the NEMO ocean model, forced by the same atmospheric fields (so-called CORE-II forcing; Large and Yeager, 2009).",
      "The three configurations used are a coarse resolution (ORCA12, ~1\u00b0), an eddy-permitting one (ORCA025, ~1/4\u00b0), and an eddy-resolving one (ORCA-R12, ~1/12\u00b0).",
      "The key finding of this work is the importance of model resolution... The coarse resolution model (ORCA12) barely produced any eddies... The eddy-permitting version (ORCA025) produced a reasonable number of eddies, but with an unrealistically fast propagation speed... The eddy-resolving model (ORCA-R12) provided the most realistic simulation, with eddy lifetimes and propagation speeds in good accord with observations..."
    ],
    "justification": "The paper performs a sensitivity analysis by comparing three configurations of the NEMO ocean model, which differ only in their horizontal resolution. The study analyzes the spread of results (e.g., eddy counts, lifetimes, propagation speeds) across these three model runs to understand the model's performance and its sensitivity to resolution. This use of a multi-model ensemble (varying a key structural parameter) to understand the range of model outcomes serves as a proxy for model uncertainty, which is characteristic of a Level 2 approach.",
