    "evidence_level": 2,
    "evidence_passages": [
      "To assess model uncertainty and to provide a multi-model perspective of the carbon balance of Northern Eurasia, we examined monthly estimates of carbon fluxes and pools over the period of 1980\u20132000 from the TEM, IBIS, and LPJ models (Hayes et al. 2011). In this analysis, the models were forced with the same historical climate, CO2, and nitrogen deposition information.",
      "The models differed significantly in their estimates of GPP, NPP, and NEP over the period of 1980\u20132000 (Fig. 6.8; see also Hayes et al. 2011). The spatial correlation between models for GPP, NPP, and NEP over Northern Eurasia was very low (mostly R < 0.2), indicating substantial disagreement in the spatial patterns of these fluxes."
    ],
    "justification": "The paper describes a model intercomparison study where multiple ecosystem models were driven by the same input data to compare their outputs. This method is a form of structured, comparative testing, analogous to a regression test in software development, used to identify major divergences or potential errors in the implementation of the models' underlying equations. This structured approach to evaluating model behavior and consistency qualifies as Level 2 evidence.",
