    "evidence_passages": [
      "Comparisons of monthly NEE simulated by the models and measured by eddy covariance towers (seven sites in European Russia and three in Siberia) show that the models reproduce the seasonal cycle of NEE with R2 ranging from 0.4 to 0.7 for individual sites and different models. All models correctly estimate the timing of the transition of NEE from positive (source of CO2 to the atmosphere) to negative (sink), but usually underestimate the amplitude of the seasonal cycle.",
      "A comparison of remote sensing estimates with ground-based data for Northern Eurasia\u2019s forests showed rather good agreement for NPP (r = 0.81), but less agreement for GPP (r = 0.52) (Fig. 6.16) (Shvidenko et al. 2008)."
    ],
    "justification": "The paper reports on the validation of multiple ecosystem models against independent, real-world data. The primary evidence describes a process-level validation of DGVMs against a network of eddy covariance towers across Northern Eurasia. This evaluation assesses the models' ability to reproduce key features of a process (the seasonal cycle of NEE, including timing and amplitude), which directly aligns with the \"Process-Level\" criterion of Level 3. The validation uses independent, site-based observational datasets, which, while not global, represent a large-scale, state-of-the-art validation approach for this regional application. Additional evidence shows statistical comparisons (Level 2) of remote-sensing products against ground-based data using correlation coefficients. The presence of the more advanced process-level validation justifies the Level 3 rating.",
