    "evidence_passages": [
      "DGVMs are designed to couple with climate models to simulate transient changes in vegetation and associated carbon and water fluxes in response to climate change.",
      "An integrated modeling framework was a key component of the NEESPI Integrated Project. This framework combined a number of process-based models, empirical approaches, and a large body of ground and remote sensing data in a system that attempted to provide a comprehensive \u2018full-cycle\u2019 (i.e., all major fluxes and pools) consistent assessment of the major components of the carbon cycle for the land territories of Northern Eurasia..."
    ],
    "justification": "The paper provides evidence that models are designed to be coupled and are used within an \"integrated modeling framework\" that combines multiple models and data sources. This shows the models are not entirely isolated and possess some form of coupling interface. However, the paper completely lacks any mention of standardized I/O formats (e.g., NetCDF, HDF5) or standardized coupling frameworks (e.g., ESMF, NUOPC). The absence of any reference to community standards for data exchange or model coupling implies that the methods used are likely proprietary or ad-hoc to the project. This aligns with the \"Proprietary I/O\" characteristic of Level 1.",
