    ],
    "justification": "The paper describes two forms of structured testing to verify the implemented algorithms. The first is the use of \"closed-loop simulations,\" where synthetic data generated from a known model is processed by the software, and the output is compared back to the original known model. This is a system-level test to verify the correctness of the algorithm and its implementation. The second method described is \"internal validation,\" which involves comparing results from different, independent processing strategies to ensure they are consistent. These methods represent structured tests of the system's mathematical correctness, which aligns with the Level 2 criteria. They go beyond simply running the code (Level 1) but do not describe the specific algorithmic checks like adjoint/Taylor tests characteristic of Level 3.",
