      "Validation of GRACE results: A popular way to validate GRACE results is to compare them with results from other space-geodetic techniques, e.g. satellite altimetry, or with outputs of hydrological or ocean models. In the following we focus on the comparison of GRACE-derived ocean bottom pressure (OBP) variations with in-situ measurements.",
      "The comparison shows in general a good agreement between GRACE and in-situ OBP. For example, the RMS of the differences between GRACE and the in-situ measurements are in the order of 1-2 cm equivalent water height and the correlation between both time series is typically 0.6-0.8."
