      "The horizontal grid is a regular spherical grid with a resolution of 1 / 48\u25e6 in latitude and longitude, which corresponds to about 2 km.",
      "The model bathymetry has been obtained by interpolating the ETOPO1 data set (Amante and Eakins, 2009) on the model grid, with local corrections in the Venice Lagoon.",
      "At the open boundary the model is forced with a one-way nesting using daily mean values from the MFS model...",
      "The results indicate the importance of having high horizontal resolution in the coastal zone, specifically in close proximity to river inputs, in order to reproduce the effect of the complex coastal morphology on the hydrodynamics. A lower resolution offshore is acceptable for the reproduction of the dense water event, even if specific vortical structures are missed."
    ],
    "justification": "The paper describes two models. The SHYFEM model uses an unstructured grid with regional refinement, varying from 5km in the open sea to 200m near the coast. The MITgcm model uses a nesting approach for its open boundary conditions. Both models incorporate realistic topography from the ETOPO1 dataset. This combination of regional grid refinement, nesting, and realistic topography directly corresponds to the Level 2 criteria: \"Refined: Nested grids or regional refinement; realistic topography\". The grids are static, not dynamically adaptive, so the work does not meet the criteria for Level 3.",
    "paper_doi": "10.5194/OS-12-51-2016",
    "paper_title": "Investigation of model capability in capturing vertical hydrodynamic coastal processes: A case study in the north Adriatic Sea"
