    "justification": "The paper evaluates a suite of climate models (CMIP5) based on their ability to simulate ocean heat content (OHC), which is a direct manifestation of the Earth's energy imbalance and thus a check on the global conservation of energy. The finding that 'The CMIP5 models show large spread in OHC changes' indicates that while the models are based on primary physics and monitor this global budget (they produce OHC as an output), the budget is not strictly or consistently enforced across the model ensemble. This leads to divergent results and suggests some models have energy 'leaks' or inconsistencies. This situation, where primary physics are present and global budgets are monitored but not strictly enforced, is characteristic of Level 2.",
