    "evidence_passages": [
      "The full-depth OHC has increased by 0.74 [0.68, 0.80]\u202f\u2009\u00d7\u2009\u202f1022\u202fJ\u202fyr\u22121 (0.46\u202fWm\u22122) and 1.22 [1.16\u20131.29]\u202f\u2009\u00d7\u2009\u202f1022\u202fJ\u202fyr\u22121 (0.75\u202fWm\u22122) for 1970\u20132005 and 1992\u20132005, respectively, with a 5 to 95\u202f% confidence interval of the median.",
      "The CMIP5 models show large spread in OHC changes, suggesting that some models are not state-of-the-art and require further improvements. However, the ensemble median has excellent agreement with our observational estimate: 0.68 [0.54\u20130.82]\u202f\u2009\u00d7\u2009\u202f1022\u202fJ\u202fyr\u22121 (0.42\u202fWm\u22122) from 1970 to 2005 and 1.25 [1.10\u20131.41]\u202f\u2009\u00d7\u2009\u202f1022\u202fJ\u202fyr\u22121 (0.77\u202fWm\u22122) from 1992 to 2005.",
      "We suggest that OHC be a fundamental metric for climate model validation and evaluation, especially for forced changes (decadal timescales)."
