      "To evaluate the dispersal simulations, we use the global drifter data from the Global Drifter Program (GDP; Lumpkin & Pazos 2007, Lumpkin et al. 2013), available from NOAA/AOML (http://www.aoml.noaa.gov/phod/dac/). ... We quantitatively compare the statistics of simulated trajectories with those of observed drifters through their zonal and meridional velocities, and their single-particle diffusivities.",
      "To further investigate the differences between model and observations, we calculate the mean zonal and meridional velocity differences (Figure 2e,f), and their root mean square errors (RMSE; Figure 2g,h) between simulated and observed velocities. Globally, the mean differences are close to zero, but the RMSE values indicate that substantial regional differences between model and observations do exist."
