      "To account for the uncertainty in the wind drag coefficient (C_d) and the uncertainty associated with the exposed area of the propagule above the water surface (A_p), we performed a series of sensitivity analyses.",
      "For the sensitivity analyses, we additionally ran the model using the lower (1.00 \u00d7 10\u22123) and upper (2.60 \u00d7 10\u22123) boundaries of the C_d reported in literature for a smooth sea surface (e.g. Garratt 1977, Wu 1980, Large & Pond 1981), and the Ap values (Table 1) were varied by \u00b150% for R. mangle (i.e. between 2.25 and 6.75 cm2) and \u00b125% for A. germinans (i.e. between 0.38 and 0.63 cm2).",
      "For each release site, a cluster of nine particles was released at the start of the simulation period (i.e. 2 November 2011 00:00:00 UTC). ... The particles were released at a depth of 0.5 m below the surface and were initially positioned on a 3 \u00d7 3 grid with a 1-km spacing in both the zonal and meridional direction, centred over the release location."
    ],
    "justification": "The paper explicitly performs sensitivity analyses on key model parameters (wind drag coefficient and exposed area of the propagule) by running the model with lower and upper bound values for these parameters. Additionally, it uses an ensemble approach by releasing a cluster of nine particles for each site to assess the impact of uncertainty in the initial release location. The resulting spread of dispersal trajectories from these multiple runs is used as a proxy for model uncertainty. This methodology, using sensitivity analysis and an ensemble of runs, directly aligns with the Level 2 criteria.",
