    "justification": "The paper uses formal, probabilistic methods to quantify uncertainty. For the GPS data, the authors explicitly state they use a Kalman filter (GLOBK software) and formal error propagation to calculate the one-sigma uncertainty of the velocities. A Kalman filter is a recursive Bayesian estimator, which is a formal probabilistic method for uncertainty quantification. For the InSAR data, the uncertainty is quantified using the standard deviation of the time series residuals, a standard statistical method for assessing the uncertainty of a linear fit. This represents a formal, data-driven probabilistic approach, thus meeting the criteria for Level 3.",
