      "The different thresholds used to define the MLD [25], the start and end of the bloom [26,27,28], or the DCM [29] could add some uncertainties to our results. However, we have chosen widely used criteria in the scientific literature and, in any case, we think that the robustness of our results, found for two very different regions such as the Bay of Biscay and the North Atlantic Subpolar Gyre, supports our main conclusions."
