    "justification": "The paper demonstrates uncertainty quantification at Level 2. For the sediment model, the author explicitly performs a sensitivity analysis by creating two \"end-member\" scenarios with varied parameters and examining the difference relative to a reference model. This directly corresponds to the \"Sensitivity analysis; spread of runs as error proxy\" criterion for Level 2. For the ocean model, the author propagates the standard deviations from the input data (temperature and salinity) to calculate the standard deviation of the output conductivity, providing a quantitative error proxy. This method, while not a full ensemble, is a model-based approach to assessing output uncertainty based on input variability, which aligns with the spirit of Level 2. The work does not involve formal Bayesian methods or posterior distributions, so it does not meet the criteria for Level 3.",
