      "To test for temporal trends in the breeding output (breeding success, hatching success, and fledging success) in both colonies combined (for which we had sufficient data, see Table 2), we used linear mixed-effects models (LMMs) from the lme4 package (Bates et al. 2015) with a binomial error distribution and a logit-link function. We used year as a continuous fixed effect, and colony as a random effect to account for between-colony variation.",
