    "justification": "The paper describes creating a historical index by applying a statistical model (General Additive Modelling - GAM) to establish an association between temperature data and zooplankton abundance. The model is then driven by historical temperature data to produce the plankton index. This is a clear example of a Level 1 'Forced' integration, where the model is entirely data-driven (based on statistical associations) rather than being based on first-principle physics or biological processes. The model logic is derived from the data, not combined with it in a sequential or synthesized manner.",
    "paper_doi": "10.1177/09596836241236332",
    "paper_title": "A Historical Plankton Index: Zooplankton abundance in the North Sea since 800 CE"
