    "evidence_passages": [
      "To address this gap, probabilistic deep learning approaches are gaining traction. Techniques like Bayesian Neural Networks (BNNs) and deep ensembles are being explored to not only fuse multimodal data but also to provide uncertainty bounds on the predictions. By treating model weights as random variables, BNNs can infer a full posterior distribution over the output, offering a principled measure of confidence.",
      "In the context of integrating data with physical laws, Bayesian Physics-Informed Neural Networks (B-PINNs) represent a key advancement for uncertainty quantification. These models use Bayesian inference to quantify uncertainties in both the learned physical parameters and the final predictions. This capability is particularly valuable for oceanography, where observation data is often sparse and noisy, and quantifying the confidence in data-driven model outputs is essential.",
      "A significant limitation of many current data integration techniques is their inability to provide reliable uncertainty estimates. Future research must prioritize the development of frameworks that can quantify the uncertainties stemming from diverse data sources, measurement errors, and model imperfections. This is crucial for building trust in multimodal ocean data products and for their effective use in operational forecasting and decision-making."
    ],
