      "Our paleo-bathymetric reconstructions can be compared with independent paleo-water depth (PWD) estimates derived from benthic foraminifera assemblages at ODP sites in Prydz Bay (e.g., Quilty, 1992; Diester-Haass, 1995; O'Brien and Leitchenkov, 2004).",
      "At Site 1165, our modeled PWD shows a general deepening trend from ~400 m in the late Eocene to ~800 m in the early Miocene, which is broadly consistent with the upper bathyal to upper-middle bathyal (200\u20131000 m) estimates from foraminifera (O'Brien and Leitchenkov, 2004) (Fig. 9a).",
      "For Site 739, our model suggests a shallowing from ~600 m to ~300 m through the Oligocene. This agrees well with the transition from middle bathyal to outer neritic environments inferred from microfossils (Quilty, 1992)."
