      "The average DOP rate was 0.78 \u00b1 0.98 (mean \u00b1 standard deviation, n = 11) mmol O2 m\u22122 d\u22121, ranging from \u22120.66 to 2.47 mmol O2 m\u22122 d\u22121. The standard deviation of the DOP rates was even larger than the mean value, and many of the DOP rates were not statistically different from zero.",
      "The precision of the Winkler titration is typically 0.1\u20130.2% (e.g., How-to-do-Winkler, n.d.), which corresponds to 0.2\u20130.5 \u03bcmol L\u22121 for a typical deep-sea oxygen concentration of 250 \u03bcmol L\u22121. This measurement error could result in an uncertainty of 0.3\u20130.8 mmol O2 m\u22122 d\u22121 for the oxygen flux calculation under their experimental conditions (i.e., sediment core with a diameter of 9.5 cm and a water overlay of \u223c1 L), which is comparable to the observed DOP rates."
