    ],
    "justification": "The paper uses a transport operator derived from a state-of-the-art, data-assimilating general circulation model (MITgcm/ECCO) that uses an adjoint-based method (the 'Green's function approach') to ensure consistency with physical laws. The authors explicitly state that 'The transport operator A is constructed to be mass-conserving.' The entire inverse method is built on the steady-state conservation equation Ac = J, where transport divergence (Ac) is strictly balanced by sources and sinks (J). This use of an adjoint-derived circulation and an explicitly mass-conserving operator to enforce a strictly closed budget for the tracer is clear evidence for Level 3.",
