    "evidence_passages": [
      "We use an ocean circulation inverse model (OCIM) to derive N2 fluxes and denitrification rates from the observed N2 distribution.",
      "The OCIM finds the steady-state tracer distribution that is most consistent with a specified circulation field, a set of interior tracer observations, and a set of tracer source/sink and boundary flux parameterizations.",
      "We solve for the tracer field x and the source/sink term b simultaneously by minimizing a quadratic cost function J... using a conjugate-gradient-based optimization algorithm. The cost function is J(x, b) = (Ax - b)^T W_m (Ax - b) + (x - x_obs)^T W_d (x - x_obs) + (b - b_prior)^T W_p (b - b_prior).",
      "The first term on the right-hand side of equation (1) penalizes deviations of the solution from the tracer conservation equation, weighted by the model error covariance matrix Wm. The second term penalizes deviations of the solution from the tracer observations xobs, weighted by the data error covariance matrix Wd. The third term penalizes deviations of the sources/sinks b from a prior estimate bprior..."
