    "justification": "The paper describes a discrete element model where sea ice is represented as an assembly of distinct, rigid polygonal bodies (ice floes). The core of the model is to simulate the dynamics and interactions of these individual floes. The boundaries of these elements are the edges of the polygons, which are inherently time-varying and moving as the floes drift, rotate, and collide. This explicit simulation of a multi-body system with constantly changing contact points and element positions directly corresponds to the 'time-varying/moving boundaries' criterion for Level 3.",
