    "justification": "The paper, which is a PhD thesis, states that the model outputs are written to ASCII files (\"fichiers ASCII\"). This represents a proprietary, non-standard I/O format. Furthermore, while the author discusses the potential for future coupling with an ocean or atmosphere model using a coupler like OASIS, they explicitly state that such coupling was not implemented as part of the thesis work (\"Un tel couplage n'a pas \u00e9t\u00e9 r\u00e9alis\u00e9 dans le cadre de cette th\u00e8se\"). The combination of proprietary I/O and the absence of any implemented coupling interfaces aligns squarely with the criteria for Level 1: Isolated.",
