  {
    "dimension": "validation",
    "has_evidence": true,
    "evidence_level": 1,
    "evidence_passages": [
      "Our model results are qualitatively consistent with these observations, with the entrainment-driven exchange flow being nearly 10 times larger than the diffusive exchange throughout most of the estuary (Fig. 4b).",
      "Here we briefly compare our TEF quantification with previous observational studies in estuaries. There are no previous studies in which both QE and QD have been directly quantified based on observations, but there is information on the signs and relative magnitudes of these terms for different estuarine regimes. Our model simulation of a fjordlike estuary indicates QE > 0 and QD < 0. This is consistent with observations from a number of fjordlike estuaries (e.g., Knight Inlet; Geyer and Cannon 1982)."
    ],
    "justification": "The paper develops a theoretical framework and tests it using a numerical simulation of a 'fjordlike estuary'. The validation against real-world data is limited to qualitative comparisons with the general understanding of such systems from previous observational studies. The authors state their model results are 'qualitatively consistent' and 'consistent with observations', which constitutes a subjective, qualitative agreement rather than a direct statistical comparison. This aligns with the criteria for Level 1.",
    "paper_doi": "10.1175/JPO-D-16-0258.1",
    "paper_title": "Total Exchange Flow, Entrainment, and Diffusive Salt Flux in Estuaries"
  },
