  {
    "dimension": "portability_scaling",
    "has_evidence": true,
    "evidence_level": 2,
    "evidence_passages": [
      "At the same time, the throughput of HPC systems has increased, following Moore\u2019s law, but this has mostly been achieved by increasing the number of processing cores and not by increasing the clock speed of individual processors. This has meant that, in order to make effective use of the available computational resources, NWP models and DA systems have had to be made increasingly parallel.",
