      "In order to explore the sensitivity of our results to the parameterization of the wave-induced sea ice fragmentation, we conducted a sensitivity experiment (hereafter SEN) where the maximum floe size Dmax has a larger value in the MIZ (3000 m) than in the CPL experiment (300 m).",
      "Our results, particularly on the sea ice lateral melt, are very sensitive to the parameterization chosen to represent the wave-induced sea ice fragmentation, and especially to the maximum floe size in the MIZ Dmax. The development of such a parameterization is, however, limited by the lack of observations to constrain it.",
