      "The ocean model component is the Finite\u2010Element Sea ice\u2010Ocean Model (FESOM) version 2 (FESOM2; Danilov et al., 2017), which is a hydrostatic ocean model formulated on unstructured meshes.",
      "FESOM2 employs an unstructured triangular mesh with 89,849 surface nodes and 47 unevenly spaced vertical z\u2010levels. The horizontal resolution varies from \u223c24 km in the Arctic to \u223c150 km in the Southern Ocean (see Figure S1 in Supporting Information S1).",
