    "justification": "The paper validates the results of its GNSS imaging method by comparing them against an independent dataset derived from GRACE/GRACE-FO satellites. The validation includes both a qualitative visual comparison of spatial patterns (evidence for Level 1) and, more importantly, a quantitative statistical analysis. The authors calculate and report Root Mean Square Error (RMSE), correlation, and Nash\u2013Sutcliffe efficiency (NSE) coefficients for time series in three key regions. The use of statistical metrics like RMSE to quantify the model's performance against real-world data directly meets the criteria for Level 2.",
