    "justification": "The paper is an observational study based on the analysis of historical tide gauge data. It focuses on statistical methods, such as harmonic analysis and extreme value analysis, to understand trends in sea level, tides, and extreme water levels. It does not describe or use a numerical model that simulates physical processes, and therefore, there is no discussion of the implementation of physical laws, conservation principles, or closed budgets, which are the core criteria for the Physics & Conservation dimension.",
