    "evidence_passages": [
      "We used a least-squares harmonic analysis to separate hourly water levels into a deterministic tidal prediction, a slowly varying MSL, and a non-tidal residual (e.g., storm surge, river flow effects)... We used the Unified Tidal Analysis and Prediction software package (UTAP) developed at the University of Hawaii (Firing et al., 1999) to perform the harmonic analysis and estimate MSL and tidal constants.",
      "To determine the long-term trend in RSL, we fit a linear trend to the annual MSL record..."
