      "The inversion is performed by minimizing the cost function J = [ ( \u03c1 m s \u2212 \u03c1 d s ) / \u03b4 \u03c1 s ] 2 + [ ( \u03c3 m s \u2212 \u03c3 d s ) / \u03b4 \u03c3 s ] 2 where the superscripts m and d refer to the modeled and data values, respectively, and \u03b4 represents the standard deviation of the data.",
      "These maps serve as inputs to models of ice-shelf evolution and sub-ice-shelf ocean circulation and their systematic production would enable monitoring of ice-shelf boundary conditions at a large scale."
