      "Here, we combine advanced time-frequency analysis with a non-stationary statistical approach to investigate the interannual-to-multidecadal modulations of the RSL in Venice since the end of the nineteenth century and how they have affected the occurrence of floods over the last 70 years.",
      "To isolate the contribution of the various factors acting at different timescales, we applied the MC-SSA to the monthly RSL time series (Sect. 2.2). We then adopted a non-stationary GEV model to evaluate how the identified multidecadal RSL variability and the long-term trend have modulated the frequency of floods over the last 70 years (Sect. 2.3)."
    ],
    "justification": "The paper's methodology is entirely based on the statistical analysis of observational time-series data using empirical methods such as Monte Carlo Singular Spectrum Analysis (MC-SSA) and a non-stationary generalized extreme value (GEV) distribution. It does not employ a physics-based model that solves fundamental equations where conservation laws would be relevant. This approach directly corresponds to the 'Empirical ... physics' and 'budgets ... are ignored' descriptions of Level 1.",
