      "Then, for a given confidence level 1 \u2212 \u03b1, the confidence interval for the k-th component of a(t) is given by \u00e2_k(t) \u00b1 z_(1\u2212\u03b1/2) * SE(\u00e2_k(t)) where SE is the standard error, the square root of the variance of the estimator, and z_(1\u2212\u03b1/2) is the (1 \u2212 \u03b1/2)-th quantile of the standard normal distribution.",
