      "The test problem is the passive advection of a cone-shaped tracer distribution in a non-divergent, rotational flow field... Since the flow field is non-divergent and purely rotational, the exact solution is a solid-body rotation of the initial shape with the period of rotation... The L2-norms of the error are shown in Table 2 for different schemes after one full rotation...",
      "We consider one-dimensional advection of a cosine bell... Table 1 shows the L2 and L\u221e norms of the error as well as the shape preservation parameter... The fourth-order scheme is clearly superior, and it shows the expected fourth-order convergence.",
