      "To confirm the robustness of the P-E field, we compared the P-E from J-OFURO3 with that from OAFlux. The spatiotemporal features of the P-E anomalies on the ENSO time scale are similar between the two data sets (not shown), giving us confidence in the robustness of the P-E field."
    ],
    "justification": "The paper validates the satellite-based sea surface salinity (SSS) data product (Aquarius) by comparing it against an independent, in-situ dataset (Argo floats). The authors provide a specific statistical metric, a correlation coefficient of 0.94, for their key study region. This use of a statistical metric to quantitatively compare a data product against independent real-world observations aligns with the criteria for Level 2. A less rigorous, qualitative comparison is also performed for the freshwater flux (P-E) datasets to ensure robustness.",
    "paper_doi": "10.1002/2017GL073573",
